@NODE "arexx" "DAPlayer V1.12 Guide"
@TOC "main"


The ARexx port name is DAPLAYER.1 for the first instance, DAPLAYER.2 for
the second instance and so on.

ARexx commands supported by DAPlayer:

These do the same as a click on the corresponding GUI button:
QUIT
PAUSE
STOP
SHUFFLE
NEXT
PREVIOUS
EJECT
HIDE
SHOW
APPEND

SORT NUMBER         sort playlist by number
SORT ARTIST         sort playlist by artist
SORT TITLE          sort playlist by title
SORT FILE           sort playlist by file name
SORT PATH           sort playlist by path and file name
SORT TYPE           sort playlist by type
sort order can be abbrevated by three letters, i.e.  NUM, ART, TIT, FIL,
PAT, TYP.

VOLUME  n           set volume in % from 0 to 400
BALANCE n           set stereo position from -100 (far left) to 100 (far
                    right). 0 is center.
SEEK    n           set current playing position to n milliseconds
REPEAT  on|off      change the state of the repeat button. Valid are on,
                    yes or 1 for on and off, no or 0 for off.

ERROR flags         set default choices in the error window. 'flags' is
                    any combination of the following:
                    S - stop playing
                    R - remove entry from playlist
                    A - apply choice to all following errors (i.e.
                        continue with next song)
                    Q - quit DAPlayer

AUDIO device/unit   set audio output device. Valid are DEVICE/22,
                    DEVICE/44, AHI/0, AHI/1, AHI/2 and AHI/3.

QUERY DURATION      return duration of the current song in milliseconds.
QUERY POSITION      return the current playing position in milliseconds.
QUERY VOLUME        return the volume setting in percent
QUERY BALANCE       return the current stereo position between -100 and
                    100.
QUERY REPEAT        return the state of the repeat button. 1 = on; 0 =
                    off
QUERY ARTIST        return the artist of the current song
QUERY ALBUM         return the album name of the current song
QUERY TITLE         return the title of the current song
QUERY FILE          return the file name (including path) of the current
                    song
QUERY NUMBER        return the number of the current song
QUERY TYPE          return the type of the current song like displayed
                    in the GUI
QUERY AUDIO         return the current audio device/unit

Query results are returned in the RESULT variable, but only if you have
set OPTIONS RESULTS in your Arexx program.
Query artist / album / title may set RC=5 if not available. In this case
RESULT remains unchanged.

@ENDNODE
@NODE "tooltypes" "DAPlayer V1.12 Guide"
@TOC "main"

Command line       Tooltype

FILE/M                              Specify one or more files or
                                    directories to load and play
                   PATH=name        Specify a file or directory to load
                                    and play
                   DRIVE=name       Specify a CD drive for playing an
                                    audio CD
DEVICE/K           DEVICE=name      Specify the device of your CD drive
UNIT/K             UNIT=number      Specify the unit number of your CD
                                    drive

Note: PATH or FILE take precedence. DRIVE only applies if PATH is not
      given. DEVICE / UNIT only apply if none of the others are given.

S=SHUFFLE/S        SHUFFLE          Shuffle the initial playlist
R=REPEAT/S         REPEAT           Enable repeat of the playlist
H=HIDE/S           HIDE             Start iconified
V=VOLUME/K/N       VOLUME=number    Set volume in % from 0 to 400
B=BALANCE/K/N      BALANCE=number   set stereo position from -100 (far
                                    left) to 100 (far right). 0 is
                                    center.
ERROR/K            ERROR=flags      set default choices in the error
                                    window. 'flags' is any combination
                                    of the following:
                                    S - stop playing
                                    R - remove entry from playlist
                                    A - apply choice to all following
                                        errors (i.e. continue with next
                                        song)
                                    Q - quit DAPlayer
NI=NOINFOS/S       NOINFOS          Do not show Artist / Album / Title
NC=NOCONTROLS/S    NOCONTROLS       Do not show control buttons and
                                    sliders
NP=NOPLAYLIST/S    NOPLAYLIST       Do not show the playlist
NV=NOCOVER/S       NOCOVER          Do not show album art
AUDIO/K            AUDIO=device     set audio output device. Valid are
                                    DEVICE/22, DEVICE/44, AHI/0, AHI/1,
                                    AHI/2 and AHI/3.

@ENDNODE
@NODE "envvars" "DAPlayer V1.12 Guide"
@TOC "main"


Some environment variables may be set to override internal default values
or to activate hidden features:


Name   :  DAPlayer/DigiBooster
Format :  VOLUME/K/N
Default:  VOLUME=10

Description

  The DigiBooster replay routine allows to set a master volume which is
  applied to the samples before mixing.

  The value specifies the dB value between -84 and +24.

Example:

  setenv DAPlayer/DigiBooster "VOLUME=0"



Name   :  DAPlayer/MIDI
Format :  VOLUME/K/N,CONFIG/K
Default:  VOLUME=50 CONFIG=timidity.cfg

Description:

  The libtimidity library allows to set a volume which is applied to the
  samples before mixing. During testing I experienced sound distortion
  with some samples, therefore I set the default volume to a rather low
  value. With this ENV variable you can override the default.
  The value is a percentage, i.e. 100 means 100%.

  The other argument is the file name of the @{"config file" LINK "midicfg"} for libtimidity.
  If you saved the config file in another place than the program directory,
  then you should specify the full path here.


Example:

  setenv DAPlayer/MIDI "VOLUME=100"



Name   :  DAPlayer/TCPTRACE
Format :  TRACE/A
Default:  OFF

  This variable specifies the output file name of an optional TCP trace.
  Every text which is sent to or received from a server will be printed
  to the trace file.

  If the file name ends with a : (like CON: for example) standard
  arguments for window size and position relative to the screen size are
  added. For example if the variable contains CON: the file opened might
  be CON:440/11/200/245/DAPlayer - TCP Trace/AUTO/CLOSE/WAIT
  if the screen size is 640x256 and the font height is 8.

Example:

  setenv DAPlayer/TCPTRACE "CON:"


@ENDNODE
@NODE "midicfg" "DAPlayer V1.12 Guide"
@TOC "main"


In order to replay MIDI files a set of patch files compatible with
Gravis Ultra Sound (GUS) are required. 

I successfully tested the popular but discontinued EAWPATS as well
as the still developed Freepats.

A configuration file needs to be created or edited so that DAPlayer
can find the patch files. By default the config file is called 
timidity.cfg. 

To use EAWPATS edit the supplied timidity.cfg file. Ignore all the
comment lines beginning with # and find the line reading 

  dir data:eawpats

Change this to the path where you unpacked the EAWPATS archive to.
Make sure that the source statements remain unchanged.
For example

  dir Work:Music/EAWPATS
  source gravis.cfg
  source gsdrums.cfg
  source gssfx.cfg
  source xgmap2.cfg


Using FreePats is similar. Make a new file called timidity.cfg which
contains two lines like these:

  dir Work:Music/FreePats
  source crude.cfg


@ENDNODE
